content.description:
A few pitches of choss followed by the best gear climbing on this end of the mountain with some bolts and bolted anchors.



From the parking of Yonge Street, head straight up to the wall above. Stay to the right in the trees. Cut left to the lowest rock below the slabs. 

A descent route in the climber's left forest is marked by flagging tap from the start of the climb.

Bolted anchors and sporadic bolts to lead the way.

From the Gripped.com article:

Gear: One 60m rope, helmet, 12 quickdrawsPitch one: Up the white slab using the left corner (5.9, 30m)Pitch two: Up left through a groove and slab (5.7, 30m)Pitch three: Up the scree/slab (3rd class, 30m)Pitch four: Up the rib left of the gully to a ridge (5.5, 30m)Pitch five: Continue up rib past bushes (5.3, 30m)Pitch six: Through the trees to a short wall (3rd class, 30m)Pitch seven: Up the wall to easier slabs above (5.6, 25m)



Approach: Park at the fifth tee at the golf course on the opposite side of the road in a small pullout. Hike down the road for 50 metres to flagging tape. Head up.

Bolted
